### Books API - Test Script
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension (install "REST Client" extension)

@baseUrl = https://localhost:5001/api/books
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Get All Books
GET {{baseUrl}}

### 2. Get Book by ID (Get first book)
GET {{baseUrl}}/1

### 3. Get Non-existent Book (Test 404 Error)
GET {{baseUrl}}/999

### 4. Create New Book
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "1984",
  "author": "George Orwell",
  "isbn": "978-0-452-26423-9",
  "publicationDate": "1949-06-08"
}

### 5. Create Another Book
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Pride and Prejudice",
  "author": "Jane Austen",
  "isbn": "978-0-141-43951-8",
  "publicationDate": "1813-01-28"
}

### 6. Update Book (Update ID 1)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "The Great Gatsby - Revised Edition",
  "author": "F. Scott Fitzgerald",
  "isbn": "978-0-7432-7356-5",
  "publicationDate": "1925-04-10"
}

### 7. Update Non-existent Book (Test 404 Error)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/999
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Non-existent",
  "author": "Nobody",
  "isbn": "000-000",
  "publicationDate": "2000-01-01"
}

### 8. Delete Book (Delete ID 2)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/2

### 9. Delete Non-existent Book (Test 404 Error)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/999

### 10. Get All Books After Changes
GET {{baseUrl}}
